    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA",
    "description": "Sobol first-order and total-order indices computed for six input parameters (Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus, yield strength, screw outer diameter, rod diameter, friction coefficient at screw-rod interface, and UHMWPE block stiffness) against all three QoIs. Elastic modulus and yield strength account for 71% of total output variance in yield force; friction coefficient contributes <4% to stiffness QoI, confirming that contact parameter uncertainty is not a dominant source of prediction error."
